The invention relates to a device for growing silicon crystals through the casting process and aims to provide a gas cooling device and method used for a polycrystalline ingot furnace. The gas cooling device is arranged in the lower part of the thermal field of the ingot furnace and the gas cooling device is a graphite body with gas channels inside. The cooling method of the invention comprises the following steps: the graphite body with gas channels is arranged in the lower part of the thermal field of the ingot furnace; and inert gas enters from the gas inlet of each gas channel, passes through the graphite body to remove heat and is discharged from the gas outlet of each gas channel. In the cooling method of the invention, the gas cooling device adopting active cooling is added at the bottom of the thermal field and the flow of the gas introduced in the device is adjusted to control the active cooling range, thus the cooling rate below the crystals can be controlled actively and the growth rate of the crystals can be controlled effectively.
